This paper discusses parallel best-first search algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) for solving problems such as planning and optimization. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the distribution of work among processes, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The analysis of search and communication overheads involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The proposal of a new work distribution method involves programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
